import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['home_score'], bins=range(0, 12), color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['home_score'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['home_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Home Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.hist(data['away_score'], bins=range(0, 12), color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['away_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Score: {:.2f}'.format(data['away_score'].mean()))
    ax.axvline(data['away_score'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Score: {:.2f}'.format(data['away_score'].median()))
    ax.set_xlabel('Away Scores')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of away scores?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['goal_difference'] = data['home_score'] - data['away_score']
    plt.hist(data['goal_difference'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['goal_difference'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['goal_difference'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['goal_difference'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['goal_difference'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Goal Difference')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of goal difference?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['count'] = 1
    data = data.groupby('division').count().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['division'], data['count'], color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of matches played by division?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Division')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Matches')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='count')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['count'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Matches Played')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of matches played by date?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
